<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,362,1774,1800]" pageId="22" pageNumber="89">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[227,920,1820,1847]" box="[227,920,1820,1847]" pageId="22" pageNumber="89">
From the Latin ‘ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel" authorityYear="2022" box="[420,510,1820,1846]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Vestinautilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="22" pageNumber="89" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="inflexus">
<emphasis box="[420,510,1820,1846]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="89">inflexus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’, referring to the incurved septum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
