<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="91" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="24.[227,341,947,973]" box="[227,341,947,973]" pageId="24" pageNumber="91">
<heading bold="true" box="[227,341,947,973]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="24" pageNumber="91" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,341,947,973]" pageId="24" pageNumber="91">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[227,1436,993,1160]" pageId="24" pageNumber="91">
<taxonomicName authority="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel, 2022" authorityName="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel" authorityYear="2022" box="[227,476,993,1019]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Vestinautilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="24" pageNumber="91" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="inflexus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[227,476,993,1019]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="91">Vestinautilus inflexus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[485,578,994,1020]" pageId="24" pageNumber="91" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
belongs to the species of the genus with a moderately depressed whorl profile (ww/wh ~1.95) and thus ranges between the more slender species 
<taxonomicName authority="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel, 2022" authorityName="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel" authorityYear="2022" box="[1091,1236,1028,1054]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Vestinautilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="24" pageNumber="91" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="angulatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1091,1236,1028,1054]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="91">V. angulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1243,1333,1029,1055]" pageId="24" pageNumber="91" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(ww/wh ~1.50) as well as 
<taxonomicName authority="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel, 2022" authorityName="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel" authorityYear="2022" box="[437,548,1063,1089]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Vestinautilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="24" pageNumber="91" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="papilio" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[437,548,1063,1089]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="91">V. papilio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[556,647,1064,1090]" pageId="24" pageNumber="91" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(ww/wh ~ 1.70) and the stouter species 
<taxonomicName authority="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel, 2022" authorityName="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel" authorityYear="2022" box="[1118,1271,1063,1089]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Vestinautilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="24" pageNumber="91" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="bicristatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1118,1271,1063,1089]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="91">V. bicristatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1278,1369,1064,1090]" pageId="24" pageNumber="91" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(ww/ wh ~2.15). The new species differs from those species of the genus with a similar whorl profile in the very weak longitudinal ridges.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
